content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 14 ยง 343.11 - Administrative fees

State Regulations
(a) Ten percent of
fees required. All certified providers must remit to the division at the end of
each eight week program 10 percent of all fees collected from program
participants to help defray the cost to the division of administering the
program. (b) Failure to remit. Failure to remit such payments may result in termination of certification in
accordance with section
343.15
of this Part or denial of
renewal of certification in accordance with section
343.14
of this Part. Notes
